						<div class="postbody">Tangentially related question that I was going to ask lidnariq eventually, sorry for the hijack.<br /><br />There's three unused pins, the two audio pins and the video pin. I was wondering how hard would it be to hook those via the bottom to a rpi or similar, to get online play. I'm a software guy, I don't really know yet how things happen on the hw wires - would it have to bitbang on both sides, using way too much cpu?<br /><br />I read that there are several protocols suitable for 3 wires or less, but even the good old serial uart bitbanging uses a lot of cpu.</div>

